---------------
Map Master Game
---------------
Authors: MI Maps Team, CS121-SoftwareDevelopment, Harvey Mudd College
Version: 0.5 using PyQt4.9
Wiki_url: https://www.cs.hmc.edu/trac/cs121sp2012_4/

------------------
Running on Windows
------------------
On Windows using the binary package is recommended.
For some versions an installer is also available.
For instructions on how to play the game see the in-game instruction page.

--------------------------
Running on other Platforms
--------------------------
MapMaster should be cross platform, and is tested regularly in scripted form on
Ubuntu Linux. MapMaster is not tested frequently on Mac OS X but should still work. In order to run MapMaster as script you will need to install:
 - Python 2.7
 - PyQt (v4.9 or compatible)
 - Pygame (v1.9.1 or compatible)

----------------------------
Build Instrucitons (Windows)
----------------------------
In order to build this program you will need the following
 - Python 2.7
 - PyQt (v4.9 or compatible)
 - Pygame (v1.9.1 or compatible)
 - Py2exe (v0.69 or compatible)

Open compile_help.py and edit the following line to contain the desired
build location.

buildLoc = normpath("../../builds/Mapmaster05")

Once you have done that run compile.py by double-clicking on it.

